      "writtenOn": "2017-11-03T13:48:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027d vote for *not* having a format compatible with the python client. In particular I think the sharding support in the client is a misfeature and should be removed, or at least it should be fixed in a much better way. So while creating a Go version we could make it much better from the start, and it wouldn\u0027t take more time to implement.\n\nThe idea is that at trigger time, we could specify a list of task requests. At collect, we would collect a list of tasks. But the task shards wouldn\u0027t have to be googletest specific anymore. wdyt?",
      "revId": "18c185eb9f9d61bdb3a79c6e5b407af6a4817d3c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
